post_cb({"20927795": {"CommentCount": "0", "ViewCount": "49", "CreationDate": "2014-01-04T22:59:29.403", "LastActivityDate": "2014-01-04T23:02:01.290", "Title": "Destruction of object in local scope", "AcceptedAnswerId": "20927819", "PostTypeId": "1", "Id": "20927795", "Score": "1", "Body": "<p>Suppose that I have the following code:</p>\n<pre><code>void foo() {  \n {\n    myclass object;\n    object.do_something();\n }\n cout&lt;&lt;\"hello\"&lt;&lt;endl;\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>Is <code>~myclass()</code> <strong>guaranteed</strong> to be called <strong>by the time the local scope is exited</strong>, or might it be called at a later time (such as when the function returns)?</p>\n", "Tags": "<c++><destructor>", "OwnerUserId": "1297272", "AnswerCount": "1"}, "20927819": {"ParentId": "20927795", "CommentCount": "0", "CreationDate": "2014-01-04T23:02:01.290", "OwnerUserId": "129570", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "20927819", "Score": "8", "Body": "<p>Yes, it is guaranteed:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_20927795_20927819_0\"><strong>[class.dtor]</strong> Destructors are invoked implicitly for ... a constructed object with automatic storage duration when the block in which the object is created exits.</p>\n</blockquote>\n", "LastActivityDate": "2014-01-04T23:02:01.290"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_20927795_20927819_0": {"section_id": 407, "quality": 0.8571428571428571, "length": 12}}, "n3337": {"so_20927795_20927819_0": {"section_id": 398, "quality": 0.8571428571428571, "length": 12}}, "n4659": {"so_20927795_20927819_0": {"section_id": 425, "quality": 0.8571428571428571, "length": 12}}}});